        {
            "title": "Conditional Formatting Practice",
            "content": "<h2 class=\"text-2xl font-bold mb-4\">Practice: Visual Analysis</h2><p class=\"mb-4\">Create a new sheet named 'Format Practice':</p><div class=\"image-frame bg-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden mb-4\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/cpWB3TB.png\" alt=\"Screenshot of how to add a new spreadsheet sheet\" /></div><div class=\"exercise-container bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg mb-6\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mb-3\">Activity 1: Highlight Large Groups</h3><p class=\"mb-2\">Apply conditional formatting to highlight groups larger than 3 people in red. Copy your formatted data to your 'Format Practice' sheet.</p><div class=\"mt-4\"><button class=\"in-tutorial-toggle w-full flex items-center justify-between p-2 bg-blue-600 bg-opacity-20 rounded-lg hover:bg-opacity-30 transition-colors duration-200\"><span class=\"text-blue-400 font-semibold\">View Solution</span><svg class=\"toggle-arrow w-5 h-5 transform transition-transform duration-200\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" d=\"M9 5l7 7-7 7\" /></svg></button><div class=\"in-tutorial-toggle-content bg-gray-800 rounded-lg mt-2 p-4\"><div class=\"image-frame bg-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden mb-4\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/jRDulEc.png\" alt=\"Conditional formatting example\" /></div><div class=\"image-frame bg-gray-600 rounded-lg shadow-md overflow-hidden mb-4\"><img src=\"https://i.imgur.com/GyyyaHq.png\" alt=\"Conditional formatting example\" /></div><ol class=\"list-decimal list-inside mb-4 space-y-2\"><li>Select column <span class=\"cell-ref\">G</span> (How many attending)</li><li>Click Conditional Formatting in the Home tab</li><li>Choose 'Highlight Cell Rules' â†’ 'Greater Than'</li><li>Enter 3 and choose 'Red Fill'</li></ol></div></div></div><div class=\"exercise-container bg-gray-800 p-4 rounded-lg mb-6\"><h3 class=\"text-xl font-semibold mb-3\">Activity 2: Colour Scale</h3><p class=\"mb-2\">Apply a colour scale to show the distribution of group sizes, using a green-to-red gradient. Copy your formatted data to your 'Format Practice' sheet. HINT: Play around with the options in Conditional Formatting.</p></div>",
